Third-party components keep their original licenses. Notable boundaries:

- The DWG converter service (LibreDWG) runs as an isolated service under
  GPL-3.0 (see ADR 0008 in docs/architecture-decisions/0008-*.md). This
  repository does NOT statically link against LibreDWG; it calls the
  service via HTTP, preserving the license boundary.

- SLM models (Phi-3 Mini, Qwen, Gemma 2) keep their respective licenses
  (MIT, Apache 2.0, Gemma Terms of Use). See src/services/slm/registry.ts.

- Bioicons (medical iconography) is MIT/CC0.

- See package.json for direct dependencies; run `npm ls --long` for full
  third-party license disclosure (SBOM target for Day-1 release per the
  consolidation plan).
